The paper discusses the usefulness of altmetrics for measuring the impact of research, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on papers being "good for teaching" suggests a stronger connection to sub-categories related to digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and sound (cs.SD).
